gn:right;\"|307,607\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|46.80\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|6,580\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio VIII]] \u2013 Appia Antica\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|131,082\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|47.29\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|2,772\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio IX]] \u2013 [[EUR, Rome|EUR]]\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|180,511\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|183.17\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|985\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio X]] \u2013 [[Ostia (Rome)|Ostia]]/Acilia\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|230,544\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|150.64\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|1,530\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio XI]] \u2013 Arvalia/Portuense\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|154,871\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|70.90\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|2,185\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio XII]] \u2013 Monte Verde\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|140,996\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|73.12\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|1,928\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio XIII]] \u2013 Aurelia\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|133,813\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|68.70\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|1,949\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio XIV]] \u2013 [[Monte Mario]]\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|190,513\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|131.30\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|1,451\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio XV]] \u2013 Cassia/Flaminia\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|158,561\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|186.70\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|849\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Presidents of the ''municipi''===\nFor the current legislature (2016\u20132021), presidents of Rome's ''municipi'' are:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable centre\"\n! N.\n! President\n! colspan=2|Party\n! colspan=2|Mayoral <br />majority\n|-\n| I\n| Sabrina Alfonsi\n| bgcolor=\"red\"| ||[[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n| \n|-\n| II\n| Francesca Del Bello\n| bgcolor=\"red\"| ||[[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n|\n|-\n| III\n| Giovanni Caudo\n|  bgcolor=\"red\"| ||[[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n|\n|-\n| IV\n| Roberta Della Casa \n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| V\n| Giovanni Boccuzzi\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| VI\n| Roberto Romanella\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| VII\n| Monica Lozzi\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| VIII\n| Amedeo Ciaccheri\n| bgcolor=\"red\"| ||[[Italian Left|SI]]\n|\n|-\n| IX\n| Dario D'Innocenti\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| X\n| Giuliana Di Pillo\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| XI\n| Mario Torelli\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| XII\n| Silvana Crescimanno\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| XIII\n| Giuseppina Castagnetta\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| XIV\n| Alfredo Campagna\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|-\n| XV\n| Stefano Simonelli\n| bgcolor=\"yellow\"| || [[Five Star Movement|M5S]]\n| {{tick}}\n|}\n\n==Urban subdivision of Rome==\nThe ''comune'' of Rome is also composed of 155 urban zones (''zone urbanistiche''), conceived as a subdivision of the ''municipi'', which were established in 1977 statistical and city planning purposes on the basis of urban homogeneity criteria. Boundaries were drafted taking account of the discontinuities in Rome's urban pattern\nThe urban zones are identified by an alphanumeric code that consists of a letter and of the number of the ''municipio'' where the zone was located: indeed, the ''municipi'' were reduced from 20 to 15 in 2013, but the alphanumeric codes were not revised.\n\n* '''[[Municipio I]]''': 1A Historic centre, 1B [[Trastevere]], 1C [[Aventino]], 1D [[Testaccio]], 1E [[Esquilino (rione of Rome)|Esquilino]], 1F [[XX Settembre]], 1G [[Celio (rione of Rome)|Celio]], 1X Archeological zone, 17A [[Prati]], 17B [[Della Vittoria (quarter of Rome)|Della Vittoria]], 17C [[Eroi]];\n* '''[[Municipio II]]''': 2A [[Villaggio Olimpico]], 2B [[Parioli]], 2C [[Flaminio (quarter of Rome)|Flaminio]], 2D [[Salario (quarter of Rome)|Salario]], 2E [[Trieste (quarter of Rome)|Trieste]], 2X [[Villa Borghese gardens|Villa Borghese]], 2Y [[Villa Ada]], 3A [[Nomentano (quarter of Rome)|Nomentano]], 3B [[San Lorenzo (Rome)|San Lorenzo]], 3X [[Universit\u00e0 (Rome)|Universit\u00e0]], 3Y [[Campo Verano|Verano]]\n* '''[[Municipio III]]''': 4A [[Monte Sacro (quarter)|Monte Sacro]], 4B [[Val Melaina]], 4C [[Monte Sacro Alto]], 4D [[Fidene]], 4E [[Serpentara]], 4F [[Casal Boccone]], 4G [[Conca d'Oro (Rome)|Conca d'Oro]], 4H [[Sacco Pastore]], 4I [[Tufello]], 4L [[Rome Urbe Airport|Aeroporto dell' Urbe]], 4M [[Settebagni]], 4N [[Bufalotta]], 4O [[Tor San Giovanni]]\n* '''[[Municipio IV]]''': 5A [[Casal Bertone]], 5B [[Casal Bruciato]], 5C [[Tiburtino Nord]], 5D [[Tiburtino Sud]], 5E [[San Basilio (quarter of Rome)|San Basilio]], 5F [[Tor Cervara]], 5G [[Pietralata (quarter)|Pietralata]], 5H [[Casal de' Pazzi]], 5I [[Sant'Alessandro (zona di Roma)|Sant'Alessandro]], 5L [[Settecamini]]\n* '''[[Municipio V]]''': 6A [[Torpignattara]], 6B [[Casilino]], 6C [[Quadraro]], 6D [[Gordiani (Rome)|Gordiani]], 7A [[Centocelle]], 7B [[Alessandrina]], 7C [[Tor Sapienza]], 7D [[La Rustica]], 7E [[Tor Tre Teste]], 7F [[Casetta Mistica]], 7G [[Centro Direzionale Centocelle]], 7H [[Omo (Rome)|Omo]]\n* '''[[Municipio VI]]''': 8A [[Torrespaccata]], 8B [[Torre Maura]], 8C [[Giardinetti-Tor Vergata]], 8D [[Acqua Vergine (Rome)|Acqua Vergine]], 8E [[Lunghezza]], 8F [[Torre Angela]], 8G [[Borghesiana]], 8H [[San Vittorino (Rome)|San Vittorino]]\n* '''[[Municipio VII]]''': 9A [[Tuscolano Nord]], 9B [[Tuscolano Sud]], 9C [[Tor Fiscale (Rome)|Tor Fiscale]], 9D [[Appio (Rome)|Appio]], 9E [[Latino (Rome)|Latino]], 10A [[Don Bosco (quarter of Rome)|Don Bosco]], 10B [[Appio Claudio (Rome)|Appio-Claudio]], 10C [[Quarto Miglio]], 10D [[Pignatelli (Rome)|Pignatelli]], 10E [[Lucrezia Romana]], 10F [[Osteria del Curato]], 10G [[Romanina]], 10H [[Gregna]], 10I [[Barcaccia (Rome)|Barcaccia]], 10L [[Morena (Rome)|Morena]], 10X [[Ciampino (Rome)|Ciampino]]\n* '''[[Municipio VIII]]''': 11A [[Ostiense]], 11B [[Valco San Paolo]], 11C [[Garbatella]], 11D [[Navigatori]], 11E [[Tor Marancia]], 11F [[Tre Fontane (Rome)|Tre Fontane]], 11G [[Grottaperfetta]], 11X [[Appia Antica Nord]], 11Y [[Appia Antica Sud]]\n* '''[[Municipio IX]]''': 12A [[Eur, Rome|Eur]], 12B [[Villaggio Giuliano]], 12C [[Torrino]], 12D [[Laurentino (Rome)|Laurentino]], 12E [[Cecchignola]], 12F [[Mezzocammino]], 12G [[Spinaceto]], 12H [[Vallerano-Castel di Leva]], 12I [[Decima (Rome)|Decima]], 12L [[Porta Medaglia]], 12M [[Castel Romano]], 12N [[Santa Palomba]], 12X [[Tor di Valle]]\n* '''[[Municipio X]]''': 13A [[Malafede (Rome)|Malafede]], 13B [[Acilia Nord]], 13C [[Acilia Sud]], 13D [[Palocco]], 13E [[Ostia Antica (district)|Ostia Antica]], 13F [[Ostia Nord]], 13G [[Ostia Sud]], 13H [[Castel Fusano]], 13I [[Infernetto]], 13X [[Castel Porziano]]\n* '''[[Municipio XI]]''': 15A [[Marconi (Rome)|Marconi]], 15B [[Portuense]], 15C [[Pian Due Torri]], 15D [[Trullo (Rome)|Trullo]], 15E [[Magliana]], 15F [[Corviale]], 15G [[Ponte Galeria]]\n* '''[[Municipio XII]]''': 16A [[Colli Portuensi]], 16B [[Buon Pastore]], 16C [[Pisana (Rome)|Pisana]], 16D [[Gianicolense]], 16E [[Massimina]], 16F [[Pantano di Grano]], 16X [[Villa Doria Pamphili|Villa Pamphili]]\n* '''[[Municipio XIII]]''': 18A [[Aurelio Sud]], 18B [[Val Cannuta]], 18C [[Fogaccia]], 18D [[Aurelio Nord]], 18E [[Casalotti di Boccea]], 18F [[Boccea]]\n* '''[[Municipio XIV]]''': 19A [[Medaglie d'Oro]], 19B [[Primavalle]], 19C [[Ottavia (Rome)|Ottavia]], 19D [[Santa Maria della Piet\u00e0 (Rome)|Santa Maria della Piet\u00e0]], 19E [[Trionfale]], 19F [[Pineto (Rome)|Pineto]], 19G [[Castelluccia (Rome)|Castelluccia]], 19H [[Santa Maria di Galeria]]\n* '''[[Municipio XV]]''': 20A [[Tor di Quinto]], 20B [[Acquatraversa]], 20C [[Tomba di Nerone]], 20D {{ill|Farnesina (Rome)|lt=Farnesina|it|Farnesina (zona di Roma)}}, 20E [[Grotta Rossa Ovest]], 20F [[Grotta Rossa Est]], 20G [[Giustiniana]], 20H [[La Storta]], 20I [[Santa Cornelia]], 20L [[Prima Porta]], 20M [[Labaro]], 20N [[Cesano (Rome)|Cesano]], 20O [[Martignano (Rome)|Martignano]], 20X [[Foro Italico]]\n\n==Historical subdivision of Rome==\nRome is also divided into 116 non-administrative units, called ''comprensori toponomastici'' (toponymic districts), which are organized into four groups:\n* 22 ''[[Rioni of Rome|rioni]]'' located in the historic centre of the city, mostly within the [[Aurelian Walls]], except for [[Prati]] and [[Borgo (rione of Rome)|Borgo]];\n* 35 ''[[Quarters of Rome|quartieri]]'' surrounding the historic centre of Rome outside the Aurelian Walls;\n* 6 ''[[Suburbs of Rome|suburbi]]'' located in the suburban area of the city;\n* 53 ''[[Zones of Rome|zone]]'' in the countryside of the ''comune''.\n\n===List of historic Rioni in Rome's centre===\n{{See also|Rioni of Rome}}\nThe ''[[Rioni of Rome|rioni]]'' originate from the [[14 regions of Augustan Rome|Regiones of ancient Rome]], which evolved in the Middle Ages into the [[14 regions of Medieval Rome|medieval rioni]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.romeartlover.it/Rioni.html |title=The \"Rioni\" of Rome |publisher=Romeartlover.it |accessdate=3 February 2010}}</ref> In the [[Renaissance]], under Pope [[Sixtus V]], they reached again the number of fourteen, and their boundaries were finally defined under [[Pope Benedict XIV]] in 1743.\n\nA new subdivision of the city under [[Napoleon]] was ephemeral, and there were no sensible changes in the organisation of the city until 1870 when Rome became the capital of Italy. The needs of the new capital led to an explosion both in the urbanisation and in the population within and outside the [[Aurelian Walls]]. In 1874 a fifteenth rione, [[Esquilino (rione of Rome)|Esquilino]], was created on the newly urbanised zone of [[Monti (rione of Rome)|Monti]]. At the beginning of the 20th century other rioni where created (the last one was Prati \u2013 the only one outside the Walls of [[Pope Urban VIII]] \u2013 in 1921). Afterward, for the new administrative subdivisions of the city the name \"quartiere\" was used. Today all the rioni are part of the first Municipio, which therefore coincides completely with the ''historical city'' (''Centro Storico'').{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n\n[[Image:Rome rioni with numbers.PNG|thumb|500px|right|A map of Rome's historic center with its [[Rioni of Rome|Rioni]].]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rione!!Name!!Population<br><small>(2016)</small>\n|-\n|R. I ||[[Monti (rione of Rome)|Monti]]||13,028\n|-\n|R. II||[[Trevi (rione of Rome)|Trevi]]||2,327\n|-\n|R. III||[[Colonna (rione of Rome)|Colonna]]||2,111\n|-\n|R. IV||[[Campus Martius|Campo Marzio]]||5,860\n|-\n|R. V||[[Ponte (rione of Rome)|Ponte]]||3,596\n|-\n|R. VI||[[Parione]]||2,572\n|-\n|R. VII||[[Regola (rione of Rome)|Regola]]||3,328\n|-\n|R. VIII||[[Sant'Eustachio (rione of Rome)|Sant'Eustachio]]||1,962\n|-\n|R. IX ||[[Pigna (rione of Rome)|Pigna]]||10,737\n|-\n|R. X||[[Campitelli]]||552\n|-\n|R. XI||[[Sant'Angelo (rione of Rome)|Sant'Angelo]]||1,084\n|-\n|R. XII||[[Ripa (rione of Rome)|Ripa]]||2,520\n|-\n|R. XIII||[[Trastevere]]||19,229\n|-\n|R. XIV||[[Borgo (rione of Rome)|Borgo]]||2,954\n|-\n|R. XV||[[Esquilino (rione of Rome)|Esquilino]]||24,167\n|-\n|R. XVI||[[Ludovisi, Lazio|Ludovisi]]||1,612\n|-\n|R. XVII||[[Sallustiano]]||2,225\n|-\n|R. XVIII||[[Castro Pretorio]]||5,341\n|-\n|R. XIX||[[Celio (rione of Rome)|Celio]]||2,519\n|-\n|R. XX||[[Testaccio]]||8,088\n|-\n|R. XXI||[[San Saba (rione of Rome)|San Saba]]||3,531\n|-\n|R. XXII||[[Prati (rione of Rome)|Prati]]||15,270\n|-\n|'''Rioni'''||'''Total'''||'''186,802'''\n|}\n\n===List of Rome's ''quartieri''===\n[[File:Mappa dei quartieri di Roma.svg|thumb|Quarters of Rome]]\n{{div col}}\n* '''Q. I''' [[Flaminio (Rome)|Flaminio]]\n* '''Q. II''' [[Parioli]]\n* '''Q. III''' [[Pinciano]]\n* '''Q. IV''' [[Salario (Roma)|Salario]]\n* '''Q. V''' [[Nomentano]]\n* '''Q. VI''' [[Tiburtino]]\n* '''Q. VII''' [[Prenestino-Labicano]]\n* '''Q. VIII''' [[Tuscolano]]\n* '''Q. IX''' [[Appio-Latino]]\n* '''Q. X''' [[Ostiense]]\n* '''Q. XI''' [[Portuense]]\n* '''Q. XII''' [[Gianicolense]]\n* '''Q. XIII''' [[Aurelio (Rome)|Aurelio]]\n* '''Q. XIV''' [[Trionfale]]\n* '''Q. XV''' [[Della Vittoria]]\n* '''Q. XVI''' [[Monte Sacro (Roma)|Monte Sacro]]\n* '''Q. XVII''' [[Trieste (Rome)|Trieste]]\n* '''Q. XVIII''' [[Tor di Quinto]]\n* '''Q. XIX''' [[Prenestino-Centocelle]]\n* '''Q. XX''' [[Ardeatino]]\n* '''Q. XXI''' [[Pietralata (Roma)|Pietralata]]\n* '''Q. XXII''' [[Collatino]]\n* '''Q. XXIII''' [[Alessandrino (Rome)|Alessandrino]]\n* '''Q. XXIV''' [[Don Bosco (Rome)|Don Bosco]]\n* '''Q. XXV''' [[Appio Claudio (Rome)|Appio Claudio]]\n* '''Q. XXVI''' [[Appio-Pignatelli]]\n* '''Q. XXVII''' [[Primavalle]]\n* '''Q. XXVIII''' [[Monte Sacro Alto]]\n* '''Q. XXIX''' [[Ponte Mammolo]]\n* '''Q. XXX''' {{ill|San Basilio (Rome)|it|San Basilio (Roma)|lt=San Basilio}}\n* '''Q. XXXI''' [[Giuliano-Dalmata]]\n* '''Q. XXXII''' [[Europa (Rome)|Europa]]\n* '''Q. XXXIII''' [[Lido di Ostia Ponente]]\n* '''Q. XXXIV''' [[Lido di Ostia Levante]]\n* '''Q. XXXV''' [[Lido di Castel Fusano]] \n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Quarters of Rome]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{commonscat-inline|Subdivisions of Rome}}\n\n{{Municipi of Rome}}\n{{Rioni of Rome}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Administrative Subdivision Of Rome}}\n[[Category:Subdivisions of Rome| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox subdivision type\n| name=               ''Municipi'' of Rome\n| map=                [[File:Roma - Municipi numerata.png|Municipi of Rome|255px]]<br />The fifth-teen Rome ''municipi''\n| category=           Local government districts\n| territory=          [[Rome]]\n| start_date=         19 January 2001\n| start_date1=\n| start_date2=\n| start_date3=\n| start_date4=\n| legislation_begin=  \n| legislation_begin\n| legislation_begin2=\n| legislation_begin3=\n| legislation_begin4=\n| legislation_end=\n| legislation_end1=\n| legislation_end2=\n| legislation_end3=\n| legislation_end4=\n| end_date=\n| end_date1=\n| end_date2=\n| end_date3=\n| end_date4=\n| current_number=    15\n| number_date=       2013\n| type=              \n| type1=             \n| type2=\n| type3=\n| type4=\n| status=            \n| status1=           \n| status2=\n| status3=\n| status4=\n| exofficio=\n| exofficio1=\n| exofficio2=\n| exofficio3=\n| exofficio4=\n| population_range=  130,000\u2013300,000\n| area_range=       20\u2013180 km<sup>2</sup>\n| government=        President <small>and</small><br>Municipal Council(s)\n| government1=      \n| government2=\n| government3=\n| government4=\n| subdivision=\n| subdivision1=\n| subdivision2=\n| subdivision3=\n| subdivision4=\n}}\nThe city of [[Rome]], [[Italy]] is divided into first-level administrative subdivisions. \n\nThere are 15 ''municipi'' (singular: ''municipio'') in the city; each ''municipio'' is governed by a president and a council who are elected directly by its residents every five years. The ''municipi'' collectively comprise the [[comune]] of Rome, which is itself one of the constituent parts of the wider [[Metropolitan cities of Italy|metropolitan city]] of [[Metropolitan City of Rome Capital|Rome Capital]].\n\n==History==\nOn 31 March 1966, for administrative purposes and to increase [[decentralization]], the territory of the ''[[comune]]'' of Rome was divided into 12 administrative areas, called ''circoscrizioni''  (singular: ''circoscrizione''). On 11 February 1972 those areas were increased to 20.\n\nOn 6 March 1992, after the [[referendum]] that ratified the separation of the then ''Circoscrizione XIV'' from Rome and the birth of the new independent ''comune'' of [[Fiumicino]], the number of administrative areas of Rome decreased to 19.\n\nOn 19 January 2001, ''circoscrizioni'' which were renamed ''municipi'' and the direct election of a President to head each ''municipio'' wa established.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strutture territoriali|publisher=Comune di Roma|accessdate=20 December 2013|url=http://www.comune.roma.it/wps/portal/pcr?jppagecode=municipi.wp|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March 2013, [[City Council of Rome|Rome City Council]] decided to merge some of the ''municipi'', reducing their number to 15 and giving them a new numeration.<ref>{{cite news|title=Roma, s\u00ec all'accorpamento dei municipi: il Consiglio li riduce da 19 a 15|url=http://www.ilmessaggero.it/roma/campidoglio/roma_municipi_accorpamento_consiglio_s_riduzione/notizie/257651.shtml#|accessdate=13 March 2013|newspaper=Il Messaggero|date=11 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==''Municipi''==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"float:left;\"\n|-\n! rowspan\"1\"  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; vertical-align:top;\" class=\"sortable\"|Municipio\n! rowspan\"1\"  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; vertical-align:top;\" class=\"sortable\"|Population <br /><small>31 December 2015</small>\n! rowspan\"1\"  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; vertical-align:top;\" class=\"sortable\"|Area <br /><small>in km\u00b2</small>\n! rowspan\"1\"  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; vertical-align:top;\" class=\"sortable\"|Density <br /><small>per km\u00b2</small>\n! rowspan\"3\"  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; vertical-align:top;\" class=\"unsortable\"|Map\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio I]] \u2013 Historical Center\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|186,802\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|19.91\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|9,382\n| rowspan=\"15\"|[[File:Roma - Municipi numerata.png|400px|The 15 Municipi of Rome]]\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio II]] \u2013 [[Parioli]]/Nomentano\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|167,736\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|19.60\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|8,567\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio III]] \u2013 Monte Sacro\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|204,514\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|97.82\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|2,091\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio IV]] \u2013 Tiburtina\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|177,084\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|49.15\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\"|3,603\n|-\n| style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray;\"|[[Municipio V]] \u2013 Prenestino/Centocelle\n|  style=\"border-bottom:1px solid gray; text-align:right;\